    • Constructor Detail

      • SetLogLevelCommand

        public SetLogLevelCommand()
        This constructor configures the new command bean to communicate with an Application Interface Server (AIS) via a default AppInterfaceConnection, instantiated automatically by the static factory method AppInterfaceConnectionFactory.createDefaultConnection(). The default connection is the client of a socket at IP address "localhost" and port defined by the int constant com.seagullsw.appinterface.comm.AppInterfaceCommunicationConstants.DEFAULT_SOCKET_PORT (e.g. 1208). Alternatively, the command bean can be configured with a different connection, for remote AIS communication via a desired socket (at a specified IP address and port number) or using HTTP, by passing that connection to the one-argument command bean constructor provided below.

      • SetLogLevelCommand

        public SetLogLevelCommand​(com.seagullsw.appinterface.client.AppInterfaceConnection connection)

      • init

        public void init()
        The command bean's init() method sets the interface function name and then calls the super method, in that order. After init(), the bean will answer true to isNew() and false to isInitialized() if any required function arguments need to be set; once all required arguments have been set, it will answer false to isNew() and true to isInitialized(). This method may be called by clients to restore the bean to its originally constructed state, in particular clearing the function arguments by initializing a new request object for the bean.
